  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Helicobacter pylori (H. pylori), which infects about 50% of the global population, has been
      recognized as a main risk factor of multiple gastric pathologies, especially non-cardiac
      gastric cancer. Strongly evidence supports that H. pylori eradication is an effective
      approach to reduce the incidence of those pathologies.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
